playlist_videos.title: Monster Jam's World Record Breaking Stunt üèÜ Revved Up Recaps Ep 6
playlist_videos.description:
MONSTER JAM is launching 10,000 toy monster trucks to break a WORLD RECORD - It's Revved Up Recaps Episode 6! We‚Äôre gonna show you how Monster Jam built the massive ramp to pull off this one-of-a-kind stunt: releasing TEN THOUSAND toy trucks down a MEGA ramp all at once!

It‚Äôs the Revved Up Recaps Making Of The 10K Stunt episode! Monster Jam is known for epic stunts! They put together an epic contest for fans the Monster Jam way! We‚Äôre gonna give you a behind the scenes look at what went into pulling off the Monster Jam 10K Truck Stunt! It took a year to figure out how to make the stunt work! They built a ramp 40-feet high and 35-feet wide and loaded it with 10,000 toy trucks! Monster Jam even set the Guinness World Record for the largest Monster Jam truck display! The trucks were arranged by color in a mosaic, so it looked just like the Monster Jam logo! Each truck had a number and each fan who entered the contest was assigned to a truck! The front row of trucks was held in place with pins! Once the pins were pulled it was game on! All the trucks raced down the ramp and went flying! The truck landing closest to the bullseye sent one lucky winner home with $10,000 and the ultimate Monster Jam prize pack!

For more Revved Up Recap videos: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLz5L2LpZEHzhmR7yK7C3YWMV_izHC8C-y

playlist_videos.title: Spin Master | The Toy Movement | Turkey 2018
playlist_videos.description:
The opportunity to play, learn, and grow ‚Äì this is the goal of The Toy Movement, Spin Master‚Äôs global initiative to spread joy to the world‚Äôs children. 

Every year, Spin Master continues its work in The Toy Movement, growing a global movement that delivers inspiration, fuels imagination, and brings happiness to children around the world. 

In 2018, a dedicated team of Spin Master employees and partner organizations travelled to Turkey to deliver 125,000 toys to displaced children. Visiting refugee camps along the Syrian border, the team met with thousands of children, spreading joy through the humble yet powerful gift of toys. 

As of 2016, 28 million children were living in forced displacement ‚Äì this includes 12 million child refugees and child asylum seekers, and 16 million children living in internal displacement due to conflict and violence. These numbers do not include 7 million children internally displaced by natural disasters.

The Toy Movement aims to show these children that they are not alone, that they are not forgotten. To learn more about our past missions and to learn how your company can join the movement, click here: http://thetoymovement.org/past-missions.php

To find more exciting Spin Master games and toys visit our website: http://www.spinmaster.com 

Join the conversation and share your photos with us on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/spinmaster

We Tweet too!! Follow us on Twitter: http://twitter.com/SpinMaster

playlist_videos.description:
Even in a prosperous country like Canada, there are still many at-risk communities with children and families living in impoverished conditions. That is why in May 2018, The Toy Movement partnered with two minor hockey organizations, The Mimico Canadiens and the Rankin Inlet Minor Hockey Association, to bring toys to kids in Canada‚Äôs far north. Hundreds of underprivileged children in the remote Inuit community of Rankin Inlet, Nunavut were surprised to receive new toys donated by Spin Master and handed out door-to-door by the young hockey players.

The players from Mimico were visiting the northern community at the edge of the Arctic Circle as part of an Experiences Canada cultural exchange program to promote minor hockey ties among the communities. When the team heard about what Spin Master was doing with the Toy Movement, they met, and an opportunity was identified to assist each other in spreading goodwill to the north.

Spin Master arranged a donation of hundreds of toys and sent personnel to accompany the mission to assist and see firsthand the joy they brought to the children. Like many northern towns, Rankin Inlet is a proud, culturally rich community but it faces the challenges of poverty, home security and an astronomically high cost of living, making even basic toys an unattainable luxury for many. The Mimico and Rankin hockey organizations along with volunteers from the Rankin community orchestrated the donation of shipping from MGA International and Calm Air and the wrapping and distribution of the toys making it a real team effort. Even the RCMP scored an assist when they helped to distribute toys to other far off hamlets by plane and snowmobile.

The players wrapped the gifts and then went door-to-door to deliver the toys to those households most in need. It was a truly heartwarming sight for many seeing kids giving back to kids. In the end it was hard to tell who had the bigger smiles, the children who received the toys or the young hockey players who felt the joy of the spirit of giving. Unlike in a hockey game, this time everyone got to win.

The Toy Movement aims to deliver inspiration, imagination, and joy to children in desperate need all over the world.

To find more exciting Spin Master games and toys visit our website: http://www.spinmaster.com 

Join the conversation and share your photos with us on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/spinmaster

We Tweet too!! Follow us on Twitter: http://twitter.com/SpinMaster

playlist_videos.title: Spin Master | Toy Movement - Nicaragua December 2017
playlist_videos.description:
On December 15th, the ORPHANetwork (ONET) and the Toy Movement brought the gift of play to 13,000 children living in impoverished areas across Nicaragua. A five-person team from Spin Master joined forces with ONET to distribute toys, just in time for Christmas.

Working with a network of Local Church Initiatives (LCIs) - which currently support 23,000 kids throughout Nicaragua - the team was able to address gifts to each child by name. For many children, this was the first time they had received a present. The moment was made even more special when children saw their name handwritten on their giftwrapped toy.

Over the course of four days, the team was able to visit LCIs in several regions of Nicaragua, including the country's capital, Managua, and the mounts of rural Matagalpa.

Behind the scenes, 135 volunteers individually wrapped 13,000 toys in less than one day. Due to the incredible partnerships, selfless volunteers, and donated toys, thousands of children began the holiday season with big smiles.

The Toy Movement aims to distribute more than 500,000 toys to 500,000 children in 2018, delivering inspiration, imagination, and joy to children in troubled parts of the world.

playlist_videos.title: Spin Master | Toy Movement - Iraq February 2018 - Family
playlist_videos.description:
Earlier this year, Spin Master distributed toys to over 40,000 children living in Gawlian camp in Northern Iraq. Partnering with Save The Children, the groups coordinated logistics, transportation, delivery and gift-wrapping. This partnership ensured toys were safely and successfully distributed to children at each of the camps.

After personally overseeing another successful Toy Movement mission, Ronnen Harary (Co-Founder of the Toy Movement, Co-CEO, and Co-Founder of Spin Master Ltd.) was delighted to touch on what makes this movement so special.

"The Toy Movement is about so much more than simply giving children toys. Regardless of their circumstances, children deserve the opportunity to grow, play and learn, and to know that they are not forgotten. Discovering a toy makes this possible, and despite the difficult circumstances these children find themselves in, we are committed to finding a way to reach kids no matter where they live."

This February's mission to Iraq marks the 6th successful Toy Movement partnership, helping to ensure that kids all over the world have the opportunity to play.

playlist_videos.title: Spin Master | Toy Movement - Mexico November 2017
playlist_videos.description:
Employees and volunteers from Spin Master and Tecma Group kicked off the holiday by hand wrapping and delivering toys to children from schools in the Ciudad area.

This special delivery to children in Juarez marks the third year in a row that the Tecma Group has joined the global initiative to give disadvantaged children in Mexico the opportunity to enjoy the feeling of fun, to be inspired and to experience the benefits of play. ‚ÄúIt is always amazing to see great companies come together to support children. Kids are the future and every little thing that we can do to help them smile and bring them happiness matters,‚Äù said Ben Gadbois. ‚ÄúThe team at Tecma have been instrumental in bringing the missions in Mexico to fruition.‚Äù

‚ÄúThe values demonstrated by Spin Master‚Äôs The Toy Movement initiative align with those of the Tecma Group,‚Äù added Toby Spoon, Tecma‚Äôs Executive Vice President. ‚ÄúThe Toy Movement initiative underscores what is important to our company and our partners. It illustrates our ideals in action.‚Äù

Spin Master and Tecma will be contacting supportive businesses in El Paso and Juarez who would like to participate in the movement. By the end of 2017, the Toy Movement is expected to have delivered more than 250,000 toys around the world.
